The paper deals with the problem of counting selected tuples from a relational database, which is a fundamental problem in database theory and falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also uses graph theory and complexity theory to analyze the problem, which suggests that it could also be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
